ctations%2C%20and%20a%20growing%20assumption%20that%20early%20movers%20will%20inevitably%20dominate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20bubbles%20are%20around%20something%20new%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20growth-stock%20boom%20of%201969%2C%20the%20subprime-mortgage%20mania%20of%202006%2C%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20in%201999%2C%20the%201720%20South%20Sea%20Bubble%2C%20and%20even%20the%20Tulip%20Craze%20of%201636%20in%20the%20Netherlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20moments%2C%20he%20added%2C%20arise%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20imagination%20is%20untrammelled%2C%20and%20it%20can%20go%20off%20in%20a%20flight%20of%20fancy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20he%20said%2C%20most%20early-stage%20companies%20don't%20survive%20the%20transition%20from%20promise%20to%20profitability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20AI%2C%20I'm%20led%20to%20believe%20that%20you%20can%20make%20binary%20bets%20in%20companies%20that%20have%20nothing%20else%20going%20on%2C%20which%20will%20be%20sink-or-swim%20bets%2C%20or%20you%20can%20invest%20in%20pre-existing%20great%20tech%20companies%2C%20which%20will%20get%20moderate%20benefits%20from%20AI%20if%20they're%20successful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a85fa8d7-ca5d-4d95-88c7-a986defd43e1%5C%22%3EWhy%20Marks%20prefers%20tech%20giants%20over%20AI%20pure%20plays%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20gamble%20on%20moonshots%2C%20Marks%20said%20he'd%20rather%20own%20stocks%20in%20established%20tech%20titans%20that%20are%20already%20generating%20profits%20%E2%80%94%20companies%20that%20can%20integrate%20AI%20as%20an%20incremental%20advantage%20rather%20than%20a%20life-or-death%20proposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20contrasted%20those%20firms%20with%20the%20fragile%20AI%20startups%20drawing%20hype%2C%20saying%20that%20Big%20Tech%20is%20positioned%20to%20reap%C2%A0some%C2%A0benefits%20from%20AI%2C%20even%20if%20the%20technology%20rolls%20out%20more%20slowly%20or%20unevenly%20than%20hoped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20breakthrough%20in%20productivity%20doesn't%20automatically%20translate%20into%20investment%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChange%20the%20world%20and%20investors%20making%20money%20are%20not%20the%20same%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarks%20echoed%20a%20warning%20Warren%20Buffett%20issued%20at%20Berkshire%20Hathaway's%202000%20annual%20meeting%2C%20when%20Buffett%20warned%20that%20the%20internet%20stock%20mania%20had%20detached%20valuations%20from%20underlying%20profit%20potential%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mistake%20he%20believes%20investors%20are%20repeating%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20same%20is%20true%20of%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhoward-marks-says-ai-hype-is-fueling-risky-moonshot-bets-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765878699000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693fea2a64858d02d216c93e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhoward-marks-says-ai-hype-is-fueling-risky-moonshot-bets-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Oaktree%20cofounder%20sees%20echoes%20of%20past%20bubbles%20in%20the%20current%20AI%20frenzy%20and%20urged%20investors%20to%20focus%20on%20durable%2C%20profitable%20tech%20giants.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhoward-marks-says-ai-hype-is-fueling-risky-moonshot-bets-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20developed%20AI%20at%20IBM.%20Here's%20how%20to%20not%20become%20intellectually%20dependent%20on%20tools.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sol%20Rashidi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693f39b564858d02d216c6d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESol%20Rashidi%20said%20she%20doesn't%20use%20AI%20to%20write%20any%20of%20her%20written%20communication.%3Cp%3ESol%20Rashidi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESol%20Rashidi%20has%20worked%20in%20AI%20for%2015%20years%2C%20scaling%20capabilities%20at%20companies%20like%20IBM.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20workers%20have%20to%20continue%20to%20use%20their%20brains%20to%20avoid%20intellectual%20dependency%20on%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERashidi%20uses%20it%20for%20acceleration%2C%20not%20replacement%2C%20and%20advises%20against%20copy%20and%20pasting%20responses.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Sol%20Rashidi%2C%20a%20former%20tech%20executive%20at%20IBM%2C%20AWS%2C%20and%20Est%C3%A9e%20Lauder%2C%20who%20is%20based%20in%20Miami.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%2015%20years%2C%20I%20have%20built%20and%20scaled%20AI%20capabilities%2C%20and%20I%20have%20over%20200%20deployments%20under%20my%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20from%20being%20an%20individual%20practitioner%20to%20running%20IBM's%20enterprise%20data%20management%20practice.%20I%20was%20the%20chief%20data%20officer%20at%20Sony%20Music%2C%20the%20chief%20analytics%20officer%20at%20Est%C3%A9e%20Lauder%2C%20and%20the%20head%20of%20technology%20for%20AWS's%20startup%20division%20in%20North%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20my%20experiences%20from%202011%20on%20have%20led%20me%20to%20realize%20there's%20a%20real%20chance%20people%20will%20develop%20a%20codependency%20on%20AI.%20So%20I'm%20focused%20on%20workforce%20preparation%20and%20educating%20the%20masses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20I%20have%20my%20own%20company%20where%20I'm%20working%20on%20solving%20the%20problem%20of%20AI%20in%20the%20workforce%20by%20teaching%20enterprises%20how%20to%20prepare%20their%20workforce%20for%20the%20future%2C%20and%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20and%20automation%20to%20amplify%20the%20workforce%20instead%20of%20eliminating%20it.%20If%20you're%20going%20to%20use%20AI%20in%20your%20day-to-day%2C%20great%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20have%20to%20be%20conscientious%2C%20to%20outsource%20tasks%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tools-are-deskilling-workers-philosophy-professor-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enot%20your%20critical%20thinking%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20need%20to%20avoid%20intellectual%20atrophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntellectual%20atrophy%20is%20when%20you%20lose%20your%20cognitive%20ability%20to%20think%20critically%20because%20you're%20outsourcing%20that%20thinking%20to%20tech.%20Just%20like%20our%20muscles%20atrophy%20if%20we%20don't%20use%20them%2C%20so%20does%20our%20brain.%20The%20big%20thing%20that%20you've%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egot%20to%20be%20careful%20of%20is%20making%20sure%20that%20generative%20AI%20doesn't%20make%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-making-workers-feel-smarter-but-worse-at-their-jobs-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethinking%20become%20generic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20everyone%20else%20is%20also%20using%20ChatGPT.%20You%20maintain%20your%20edge%20by%20using%20cognitive%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cfad4350-c2ad-4b8d-b0de-981ebd226f91%5C%22%3EDon't%20replace%20your%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20individual%2C%20I%20use%20six%20to%20eight%20AI%20tools%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eevery%20day.%20I%20use%20AI%20a%20lot%20for%20data%20processing%2C%20so%20I%20can%20think%20about%20the%20patterns%20and%20insights%20and%2C%20from%20there%2C%20observe%20and%20spotlight%20frameworks%20and%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20using%20the%20tools%2C%20I%20always%20ask%20myself%2C%20%26quot%3BAm%20I%20using%20this%20to%20accelerate%20work%20I%20have%20to%20do%2C%20or%20am%20I%20using%20it%20to%20do%20the%20work%20for%20me%3F%26quot%3B%20It%20needs%20to%20accelerate%20the%20work%20so%20that%20the%20thinking%20is%20left%20to%20me.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20making%20me%20faster%2C%20but%20is%20it%20making%20me%20more%20capable%3F%20This%20is%20making%20me%20more%20productive%2C%20but%20is%20this%20making%20me%20more%20valuable%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20use%20the%20tools%20to%20expedite%20and%20facilitate%20versus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-is-letting-employees-slack-off-by-cutting-workloads-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edoing%20the%20work%20for%20me%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20what%20I%20do%20is%20communication%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20ever%20want%20to%20lose%20that%20edge.%20I%20don't%20use%20AI%20to%20write%20emails%2C%20keynotes%2C%20or%20personal%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20really%20important%20for%20me%20to%20be%20able%20to%20understand%20whether%20or%20not%20what%20I'm%20communicating%20is%20being%20perceived%20in%20the%20way%20I%20intended.%20That%20takes%20practice.%20Anything%20that%20comes%20from%20the%20heart%20or%20mind%20has%20to%20be%20sincere%2C%20expressive%2C%20and%20communicate%20the%20right%20messaging.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20organically%20generated%20by%20me%20%E2%80%94%20no%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224bbf12bf-2ecc-4fbe-9456-e88eb809355f%5C%22%3EDon't%20copy%20and%20paste%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20live%20in%20a%20society%20right%20now%20that%20values%20convenience%20over%20competition%20and%20speed%20over%20substance.%20But%20the%20key%20to%20keeping%20up%20is%20actually%20slowing%20down%2C%20because%20there%20is%20no%20shortage%20of%20information%20coming%20to%20us.%20We're%20ingesting%20so%20many%20gigabytes%20of%20data%20every%20day%20through%20WhatsApp%2C%20Slack%2C%20email%2C%20LinkedIn%2C%20and%20Instagram.%20The%20way%20we%20used%20to%20handle%20the%20workload%20of%20the%20past%20cannot%20be%20replicated%20to%20handle%20the%20speed%20of%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20have%20to%20develop%20our%20discernment%20muscles%2C%20which%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20spot%20a%20signal%20from%20noise.%20A%20large%20percentage%20of%20content%20worldwide%20right%20now%20is%20AI-generated%2C%20and%20we%20have%20AI-generated%20content%20that%20is%20being%20cannibalized%20to%20retrain%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20forward%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20get%20to%20the%20point%20of%20diminishing%20return.%20Problem-solving%20skills%20are%20going%20to%20be%20so%20important%2C%20and%20it%20will%20be%20super%20important%20to%20discern%2C%20validate%2C%20and%20verify%20AI%20responses.%20You%20can%20use%20AI%20to%20author%20the%20first%20draft%2C%20but%20maybe%20don't%20copy%20and%20paste%20the%20output%20because%20it's%20often%20inaccurate.%20Think%20of%20it%20as%20a%20first%20draft%20always.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20team%20that%20I%20managed%20was%20a%20data%20science%20team%20at%20a%20Fortune%20500%20company.%20I%20tasked%20my%20junior%20and%20senior%20data%20scientists%20to%20come%20up%20with%20an%20approach%20for%20the%20CMO%20for%20a%20new%20product.%20My%20junior%20scientist%20produced%20the%20same%20deliverable%20as%20the%20senior%20scientists%20but%20it%20took%20them%20less%20than%20half%20the%20time%20because%20they%20took%20the%20word%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounded%20great%2C%20but%20they%20short-circuited%20the%20process%20of%20research%20and%20verification%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20make%20a%20new%20mandate%20that%20they%20cannot%20use%20AI%20to%20do%20the%20work%20for%20them%2C%20but%20only%20to%20help%20facilitate%20and%20accelerate%20the%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20my%20junior%20scientists%20and%20anyone%20highly%20codependent%20on%20AI%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20paying%20for%20your%20brain%20and%20uniqueness.%20I'm%20not%20paying%20you%20to%20copy%20and%20paste%2C%20because%2C%20quite%20frankly%2C%20a%20license%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C