Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-jpmorgan-father-rto-mandate-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJPMorgan%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20required%20to%20come%20back%20found%20themselves%20in%20a%20sort%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2025%2F03%2F06%2Fjpmorgan-chase-jamie-dimon-union-rto-wall-street%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHunger%20Games%20situation%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20spots%2C%20showing%20up%20extra%20early%20and%20leaving%20behind%20possessions%20to%20mark%20their%20spots%20and%20signing%20on%20from%20vacation%20to%20try%20to%20book%20scarce%20desk%20space.%20On%20Reddit%2C%20some%20employees%20described%20the%20situation%20as%20%26quot%3Bpure%20chaos%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20complained%20of%20being%20unable%20to%20accomplish%20work%20because%20%26quot%3Bhalf%20the%20morning%20is%20spent%20on%20desk%20f***ery.%26quot%3B%20One%20JPMorgan%20employee%20told%20me%20that%20they%20often%20find%20themselves%20seated%20far%20away%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20team%20because%20someone%20else%20reserved%20their%20regular%20spot%2C%20and%20there%20are%20often%20lines%20for%20the%20women's%20bathroom%20at%20the%20New%20York%20office%20where%20they%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20office%20space%20is%20needed%20and%20what%20to%20do%20with%20it%20is%20a%20perpetual%20conundrum.%20Just%20look%20at%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-open-office-makes-you-distracted-exhausted-and-insecure-2014-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehate%20for%20open-office%20floor%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20pandemic%20added%20more%20complications%20to%20an%20already%20complicated%20situation.%20As%20the%20RTO%20wave%20has%20picked%20up%20momentum%2C%20space%20has%20become%20a%20significant%20issue%20at%20many%20companies%2C%20both%20large%20and%20small%2C%20including%20giant%20federal%20agencies.%20So%20what%20gives%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20it%20is%20simply%20a%20result%20of%20poor%20planning%2C%20explains%20Nick%20Bloom%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20Stanford%20University%20who%20studies%20remote%20work.%20Decisions%20are%20made%20at%20the%20executive%20level%20without%20proper%20consultation%20with%20facilities%20personnel%2C%20who%20have%20detailed%20information%20on%20desks%20and%20seating.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20as%20easy%20as%20adding%20up%20people%20and%20comparing%20to%20desks%2C%20as%20it%20matters%20which%20cities%20and%20offices%20they%20are%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BKind%20of%20like%20airlines%20that%20some%20flights%20may%20be%20overbooked%20and%20others%20half-empty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20shortages%20may%20be%20on%20purpose.%20Strict%20RTO%20mandates%20are%20often%20viewed%2C%20at%20least%20in%20part%2C%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-driving-workers-quit-helping-employers-avoid-layoffs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoft%20layoff%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20companies%20expect%20some%20level%20of%20attrition%20when%20they%20force%20people%20back%2C%20even%20if%20they%20won't%20openly%20admit%20it.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20insufficient%20seating%20is%20all%20part%20of%20the%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20a%2010%25%20head%20count%20reduction%2C%20you%20only%20need%20seating%20for%2090%25%20of%20the%20folks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Elliott%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Work%20Forward%2C%20a%20future%20of%20work%20think%20tank%20and%20consultancy%2C%20says%20that%20when%20executives%20started%20to%20think%20about%20bringing%20people%20back%20to%20the%20office%20in%20about%202021%2C%20many%20were%20surprised%20to%20learn%20how%20low%20the%20percentage%20of%20their%20workforce%20actually%20showing%20up%20on%20a%20given%20day%20had%20been%20pre-2020%2C%20because%20of%20sick%20time%2C%20vacations%2C%20workers%20visiting%20customers%2C%20etc.%20%26quot%3BSo%20your%20average%20CFO%20looks%20at%20this%20and%20goes%2C%20'It's%20a%2060%25%20utilized%20asset%20on%20average.%20Why%20am%20I%20doing%20assigned%20seating%3F%20Why%20not%20go%20to%20hoteling%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhot-bedding-definition-share-bed-with-stranger-save-money-rent-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehot%20desking%3C%2Fa%3E%3F'%26quot%3B%20Elliott%20says.%20Add%20in%20the%20belief%20that%20at%20least%20some%20sort%20of%20remote%20work%20would%20stick%20around%20(especially%20as%20companies%20offered%20it%20as%20a%20perk%20to%20attract%20workers%20in%20a%20tight%20labor%20market)%2C%20and%20many%20companies%20decided%20to%20downsize%20their%20overall%20office%20footprint%20to%20save%20some%20cash.%20Now%2C%20as%20businesses%20decide%20they%20want%20everyone%20back%20in%20full-time%2C%20they're%20realizing%20they%20axed%20too%20many%20desks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20are%20moving%20in%20the%20other%20direction%2C%20and%20are%20on%20the%20hunt%20for%20more%20spacious%20offices.%20But%20that%20process%20takes%20time%2C%20and%20economic%20uncertainty%20has%20leaders%20nervous%20to%20go%20too%20big.%20Commercial%20real%20estate%20services%20and%20investment%20firm%20CBRE%20says%20economic%20jitters%2C%20high%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20slow%20growth%20in%20in-person%20jobs%20has%20been%20somewhat%20of%20a%20drag%20on%20office%20leasing%20activity%20this%20year%2C%20but%20the%20overall%20trend%20is%20up%3A%20A%20growing%20majority%20of%20its%20office%20occupants%20expect%20to%20maintain%20or%20expand%20their%20space%20over%20the%20next%20three%20years%2C%20while%20the%20share%20anticipating%20downsizing%20is%20steadily%20decreasing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20are%20taking%20more%20spaces%2C%20so%20clearly%2C%20they%20are%20very%20comfortable%20in%20expansionary%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Henry%20Chin%2C%20global%20head%20of%20research%20at%20CBRE.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20employees%20should%20expect%20to%20be%20drowning%20in%20spacious%20offices%20anytime%20soon%20%E2%80%94%20businesses%20are%20driving%20toward%20%3Cem%3Ehigher%20%3C%2Fem%3Epeople-to-desk%20ratios%2C%20not%20lower.%20So%20instead%20of%20a%20single%20assigned%20desk%20for%20every%20person%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20people%20sharing.%20Per%20CBRE%2C%20the%20most%20common%20ratio%20today%20is%201-1.49%20employees%20per%20seat%2C%20and%20the%20plan%20is%20to%20up%20it.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20they%20want%20to%20have%20the%20higher%20ratio%2C%20that%20two%20or%20three%20people%20share%20a%20desk%2C%26quot%3B%20Chin%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20however%20you%20feel%20about%20hotel%20desking%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20get%20used%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20RTO%20battle%20in%20America%20is%20proving%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffight-return-to-office-mandates-remote-work-amazon-apple-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equite%20the%20push-and-pull.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Remote%20work%20is%20falling%2C%20but%20it%20hasn't%20gone%20away%3A%20According%20to%20Bloom's%20tracker%2C%20about%2025%25%20of%20work%20is%20being%20done%20from%20home%20in%20the%20US%2C%20compared%20to%2062%25%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202020%2C%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20well%20under%2010%25%20prior%20to%20the%20lockdowns.%20And%20just%20because%20companies%20ask%20workers%20to%20come%20back%20doesn't%20mean%20they're%20all%20complying%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20a%20delta%20between%20what%20employers%20are%20asking%2C%20and%20employees%20are%20giving%2C%20RTO-wise.%20As%20the%20job%20market%20weakens%2C%20employees%20may%20be%20inclined%20to%20give%20in%20and%20commute%20more.%20You%20want%20your%20boss%20to%20see%20you%20enough%20that%20they%20at%20least%20feel%20a%20little%20guilty%20when%20they%20fire%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20space-related%20headaches%20are%20reflective%20of%20broader%20questions%20about%20where%20and%20how%20it's%20best%20for%20people%20to%20work%2C%20and%20what%20sort%20of%20planning%20needs%20to%20be%20put%20into%20it.%20Some%20executives%20seem%20to%20be%20knee-jerk%20demanding%20people%20come%20back%20in%20without%20considering%20whether%20that's%20how%20their%20teams%20work%20best%2C%20or%20whether%20the%20infrastructure%20can%20handle%20it.%20A%20five-day-a-week%20office%20mandate%20isn't%20super%20helpful%20if%20teams%20are%20located%20all%20over%20the%20country%20and%20everyone's%20just%20sitting%20on%20video%20calls%20all%20day.%20Some%20companies%20are%20discovering%20they%20need%20more%20small%20meeting%20rooms%2C%20not%20just%20a%20few%20large%20ones%2C%20so%20people%20can%20gather%20if%20they%20are%20in%20the%20same%20place.%20And%20some%20are%20falling%20short%20on%20basic%20blocking%20and%20tackling%20%E2%80%94%20having%20working%20WiFi%2C%20or%20supplying%20sufficient%20monitors%20and%20equipment.%20In%20the%20internet%20age%2C%20it's%20a%20little%20tough%20to%20get%20work%20done%20when%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20internet%20itself%2C%20or%20a%20keyboard%20or%20a%20mouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20may%20be%20%26quot%3Bconflating%20productivity%20and%20effectiveness%20with%20proximity%26quot%3B%20in%20insisting%20people%20show%20up%20full-time%2C%20explains%20Melissa%20Daimler%2C%20a%20corporate%20culture%20consultant.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20can%20see%20you%20and%20I%20know%20that%20you're%20working%2C%20then%20I%20feel%20good%20about%20how%20productive%20we%20are%20as%20a%20company.%26quot%3B%20Much%20of%20the%20issue%20comes%20down%20to%20trust%20%E2%80%94%20businesses%20feeling%20confident%20that%20their%20people%20will%20get%20the%20work%20done%20when%20they're%20in%20the%20office%20collaborating%20and%20when%20they're%20at%20home%20for%20the%20day.%20%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20an%20extra%20kind%20of%20set%20of%20planning%20skills%20and%20a%20system%20that%20you%20put%20in%20place%20as%20a%20company%20and%20a%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20problem%20is%20one%20that%20companies%20%3Cem%3Eshould%20%3C%2Fem%3Efix%2C%20whether%20they%20actually%20will%20is%20another%20question.%20Your%20employees%20aren't%20going%20to%20love%20the%20return%20of%20long%20commutes%20and%20sad%20salad%20desk%20lunches%2C%20whatever%20you%20do%2C%20but%20they're%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20even%20more%20annoyed%20if%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20that%20commute%2C%20they%20find%20themselves%20eating%20that%20sad%20salad%20on%20the%20floor%20in%20the%20hallway%2C%20seated%20next%20to%20their%20laptop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-amazon-jpmorgan-instagram-att-seats-desks-office-space-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765876621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694073ab64858d02d216d55a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-amazon-jpmorgan-instagram-att-seats-desks-office-space-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20like%20AT%26amp%3BT%2C%20Amazon%2C%20JPMorgan%2C%20and%20Instagram%20have%20a%20RTO%20problem%3A%20there's%20not%20enough%20places%20for%20workers%20to%20sit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-amazon-jpmorgan-instagram-att-seats-desks-office-space-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anupam%20pens%20emotional%20note%20a